  <main id="main" class="container" role="main">
    <h1>Web App Manifest</h1>
    <div class="card">
      <p>The manifest is a JSON file that describes your app’s name, icons, colors, and how it should launch. It’s linked from <code>index.html</code> using <code>&lt;link rel="manifest" href="manifest.json"&gt;</code>.</p>
      <table class="table-like">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>name</code>, <code>short_name</code></td><td>Display names for install UI and home screen.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>icons</code></td><td>Icon set for various sizes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>theme_color</code>, <code>background_color</code></td><td>Brand/app shell colors.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>start_url</code>, <code>scope</code></td><td>Where the app starts and routing scope.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>display</code></td><td>Standalone, fullscreen, minimal-ui, or browser.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </main>

